div.div:
Note: 3:1 stands forExponential Moving Average (EMA)
EMA = ((old_avg * 3) + new_val) / 4
In RTL:
With Multiplier:
((old_avg * 3) + new_val) >> 2
Without Multiplier:
((old_avg <<1) + old_avg + new_val) >> 2
or
((old_avg <<2) - old_avg + new_val) >> 2
